  "font": {
    "basel": {
      "$value": "Basel",
      "$type": "fontFamily",
      "$description": "Sole typeface across every UI surface. The unusual mid-weights (485, 535) are the signature: Basel avoids the standard 400/500/600 ladder and instead calibrates precise intermediate weights, which is why body text and headings feel more like a continuous gradient than discrete steps. The geometric construction with tight -0.02em tracking across all sizes produces a slightly compressed, clinical-financial tone — readable but never decorative. For open-source replacement use Inter at 400/500/550, or DM Sans at 400/500/550."
    }
  },
